</div>

<h2 id="measuring-success">📊 Measuring Retention Automation Success</h2>

You can't improve what you don't measure. Here are the KPIs our team tracks for every retention automation deployment:

**Primary Metrics:**
- Monthly churn rate (target: under 3%)
- 90-day new member retention (target: over 70%)
- Intervention response rate (target: over 20%)
- Win-back conversion rate (target: over 10%)

**Secondary Metrics:**
- Average tenure at cancellation
- Engagement score distribution
- Revenue retained (directly attributable to automation)
- Staff time saved on manual outreach

Build a dashboard that surfaces these weekly. When numbers trend wrong, you'll catch it before a small problem becomes a major leak.

